Sentencas: Ni particle coarsening is an important factor in deteriorating the durability of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operations.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: In order to investigate the influence of Ni coarsening on SOFC performance, the transient multi-physical field model of SOFC was developed in this paper.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: The high operating temperature accelerates Ni particle growth and increases the attenuation rate of SOFC current density from 0.23%/kh at 650 degrees C to 2.6%/kh at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: The increase in the ratio of steam to carbon also intensifies the Ni particle coarsening process and deteriorates the transient performance of SOFC.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: Increasing YSZ particle diameter could hinder the growth of Ni particles and slowing down the increase rate of Ni particle diameter.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: Within the range of preset YSZ diameter dYSZ, increasing dYSZ reduces the attenuation rate and increases the average current density.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: Improving Ni phase fraction helps to reduce the attenuation rate of current density.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: Since multi-physical field (MPF) simulation needs long calculation time and it is difficult to achieve fast prediction, artificial neural network (ANN) is trained by the database generated by MPF.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: The mapping relationship between operating parameters, structural parameters and attenuation indexes is obtained.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: Finally, the attenuation performance of SOFC is optimized by genetic algorithm (GA) through data-driven method.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: The absolute average relative errors of all parameters in predicting attenuation rate and average current density are as low as 0.767% and 0.248%, which indicates the reliability of the ANN prediction.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: After optimization, the maximum current density is 5848 A.m(-2) under operating voltage at 0.6 V when the attenuation rate requirement not exceeding 1% is satisfied.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network

Sentencas: The combination of MPF simulation, ANN and GA provides a framework for fast performance prediction and optimization of strong nonlinear system.
Titulo: Ni coarsening and performance attenuation prediction of biomass syngas fueled SOFC by combining multi-physics field modeling and artificial neural network
